WHEREAS, lack of quality, affordable early childhood education not only affects
the workforce of tomorrow, but also has a substantial impact on the workforce of today, in
terms of both worker participation and productivity in Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, research has shown that there can be a thirteen percent return on public
investment in quality, affordable early childhood education; and
WHEREAS, child care issues and lost workforce participation and productivity have
resulted in a more than a one billion three hundred million dollar loss for Louisiana's
economy; and
WHEREAS, the over two hundred organizations from across Louisiana that comprise
the Ready Louisiana Coalition are working to provide access to quality, affordable early
childhood education to improve children's outcomes, strengthen their families, and build the
economy.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby designate Tuesday, May 19, 2026, as Early Ed Day at the Louisiana State
Capitol and commends the Ready Louisiana Coalition.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
Ready Louisiana Coalition.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
